            <div>
                <!-- <addrLine> Salomonstr [Bleistift] </addrLine> -->
                <opener>
                    <salute>
                        <lb/>
                        My darling
                        <persName key="##"> mother, </persName>
                        .
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    Dont be alarmed
                    <hi rend="strikethrough">
                        <unclear> </unclear>
                    </hi>
                    at seeing a strange handwiting -
                    <lb/>
                    I'm in Bed but not sick
                    <lb/>
                    "unto death", my nerves have
                    <lb/>
                    been rather knocked up for
                    <lb/>
                    some time and now my
                    <lb/>
                    unhappy heart has to bear
                    <lb/>
                    the brunt of it. I have
                    <lb/>
                    been sent to bed in order to
                    <lb/>
                    reduce the palpitation and
                    <lb/>
                    here may have to stay
                    <lb/>
                    for a day or two longer, in
                    <lb/>
                    all about a week. Don't think
                    <lb/>
                    mother darling, that I have
                    <lb/>
                    been left entirely on my
                    <lb/>
                    own hook. I have been
                    <hi rend="superscript">nursed </hi>
                    <!-- 'nursed' vermutlich nachträglich eingefügt. -->
                    <lb/>
                    during this week
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    as well as I ever was in my life both
                    <lb/>
                    night and day, but as
                    <persName key="Herzogenberg, Elisabeth von" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/124263690">
                        the
                        <lb/>
                        instrument of my recovery
                    </persName>
                    <lb/>
                    happened to be writing this
                    <lb/>
                    for me I will tell you
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="strikesthough"> more </hi>
                    <hi rend="superscript">all</hi>
                    about it, when I
                    <lb/>
                    can write to you myself.
                    <lb/>
                    (the poor
                    <persName key="Herzogenberg, Elisabeth von" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/124263690">
                        <lb/>
                        <del rend="overstrike">emanuensis</del>
                        <add place="above">amanuensis</add>
                    </persName>
                    is
                    <lb/>
                    suffering severely from writing
                    <lb/>
                    the accompanying!)
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    And now please
                    <persName key="Nina Smyth" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118883658">mother </persName>
                    <lb/>
                    listen attentively to what's
                    <lb/>
                    coming.;
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    1
                    <hi rend="superscript">
                        <hi rend="underline">
                            <hi rend="underline">o</hi>
                        </hi>
                    </hi>
                    there's no disease of
                    <lb/>
                    the heart but if I didn't
                    <lb/>
                    take care of myself
                    <lb/>
                    during the next few
                    <lb/>
                    months it might become
                    <lb/>
                    so. The doctor says seeing
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    that the heat is already
                    <lb/>
                    very severe in
                    <settlement key="Leipzig" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/4035206-7">Leipzig </settlement>
                    and
                    <lb/>
                    will of course become more
                    <lb/>
                    so, I should have but a
                    <lb/>
                    poor chance of
                    <del rend="overstrike">putting</del>
                    <add place="above">pulling</add>
                    <!--t-Striche mit Bleistift durchgestrichen-->
                    <lb/>
                    together again if I stay
                    <lb/>
                    on here long. Added to
                    <lb/>
                    this I should of course
                    <lb/>
                    be unable to visit the
                    <lb/>
                    <placeName key="Königliches Konservatorium zu Leipzig" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/5039621-3">Conservatorium</placeName>
                    . This is
                    <lb/>
                    no misfortune because
                    <lb/>
                    as you know I have
                    <lb/>
                    already begun my course
                    <lb/>
                    of instruction with
                    <lb/>
                    <persName key="Herzogenberg, Heinrich von" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/119523876">Herr von Herzogenberg</persName>
                    <lb/>
                    and he has mapped
                    <lb/>
                    out for me the contrapuntae
                    <lb/>
                    root which I am to
                    <lb/>
                    follow during the
                    <del rend="overstrike">holydays</del>
                    <add place="above">holy days</add>
                    <!--
                        Verbindung zwischen y und d nachträglich mit Bleistift durchgestrichen
                    -->
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    until we resume the thread
                    <lb/>
                    of our discourse in the
                    <lb/>
                    autumn. As the ways in
                    <lb/>
                    the
                    <placeName key="Königliches Konservatorium zu Leipzig" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/5039621-3">Conservatorium</placeName>
                    are not
                    <lb/>
                    like unto his ways it's
                    <lb/>
                    just as well, noy even better
                    <lb/>
                    that I
                    <choice>
                        <sic cert="high">should'nt</sic>
                        <corr>shouldn't</corr>
                    </choice>
                    mix
                    <lb/>
                    up the two, in my unfortu
                    <lb/>
                    nate cerebrum. When I
                    <lb/>
                    am at home I am afraid
                    <lb/>
                    I shall have, at first at all
                    <lb/>
                    events, to live rather dif-
                    <lb/>
                    ferently
                    <hi rend="strikethrough"> for </hi>
                    from to what I ex-
                    <lb/>
                    pected. for it is not the
                    <lb/>
                    work I shall do that
                    <lb/>
                    will kusel me up but
                    <lb/>
                    the return to the old
                    <lb/>
                    life I used to lead
                    <del rend="overstrike">auch</del>
                    <add place="above">in</add>
                    <lb/>
                    the palmy days of cakes
                    <lb/>
                    and ale. This you will
                    <lb/>
                    understand when I tell you
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    that the things I am at present
                    <lb/>
                    forbidden are flopping about
                    <lb/>
                    in bed, talking bond
                    <lb/>
                    (from which she is very
                    <lb/>
                    difficult to be kept back)
                    <lb/>
                    gesticulating and following
                    <lb/>
                    the natural impulses of
                    <lb/>
                    my depraved nature.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    Of course I am at present
                    <lb/>
                    also forbidden to do any
                    <lb/>
                    sort of work or anything
                    <lb/>
                    that egites me, for it
                    <lb/>
                    takes but little to make
                    <lb/>
                    my heart beat like
                    <add place="inline">a</add>
                    bell
                    <lb/>
                    clapper.
                    <hi rend="strikethrough">
                        <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    </hi>
                    As regards
                    <lb/>
                    details I have had little
                    <lb/>
                    or no pain; in fact the
                    <lb/>
                    whole thing is not dangerous
                    <lb/>
                    but my health for some
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    time depends upon whether
                    <lb/>
                    I take proper care of myself after this crisis. After a
                    <lb/>
                    fourtnight my work will
                    <lb/>
                    easily be in no way affected by it.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    I leave it to you to say
                    <lb/>
                    of as the Doctor advices
                    <lb/>
                    I shall come home
                    <lb/>
                    as soon as I am well
                    <lb/>
                    enough to travel. When
                    <lb/>
                    you have had enough
                    <lb/>
                    of
                    <hi rend="strikethrough">y</hi>
                    me at home! I
                    <lb/>
                    could come back to Germany
                    <lb/>
                    and establish myself
                    <lb/>
                    with
                    <persName key="Friedlaender, Max" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/116797673"> Friedländers </persName>
                    at
                    <settlement key="Friedrichroda" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/4018592-8">
                        Friedrich
                        <lb/>
                        Roda
                    </settlement>
                    or some such place
                    <lb/>
                    but I don't think the
                    <lb/>
                    gaieties at home will
                    <lb/>
                    tempt me from my
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    work. Well, That's about all. It
                    <lb/>
                    only remaines to tell you
                    <lb/>
                    not to be anxious about
                    <lb/>
                    me. You'll find me looking as well as ever
                    <lb/>
                    and alas as inchired
                    <lb/>
                    to "gather the rosebuds
                    <lb/>
                    while I may" as of
                    <lb/>
                    yore. Write soon and
                    <lb/>
                    give me your opinion,
                    <lb/>
                    on all this. Best love
                    <lb/>
                    to all and many thanks to Violet for
                    <lb/>
                    her letter which I of
                    <lb/>
                    course
                    <hi rend="underlined"> cannot </hi>
                    answer
                    <lb/>
                    now, or I would.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    I am fairly on the
                    <lb/>
                    road of to recovery
                    <lb/>
                    and will get up.
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    tomorrow.
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <lb/>
                        Ever your devoted child
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <lb/>
                        Ethel.
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <lb/>
                        (
                        <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        cannot help
                        <lb/>
                        saying that she enjoyed
                        <lb/>
                        meeting your dear
                        <lb/>
                        child so very much;
                        <lb/>
                        also she must assure
                        <lb/>
                        you that you have not
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="strikethrough"> can not</hi>
                        the least
                        <lb/>
                        occasion more to be discomforted about Ethel.)
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <lb/>
                        1
                        <hi rend="superscript">st</hi>
                        letter
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="strikethrough">
                            <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        </hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="strikethrough">
                            <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        </hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="strikethrough">
                            <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        </hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="strikethrough">
                            <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        </hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="strikethrough">
                            <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        </hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
